rstate; Lynn was thrown clear of the car and her mother died at the scene.<ref name=Playboy115>{{cite journal|author= Mike Sager|date=September 2011|title= The Porn Identity|journal= [[Playboy (magazine)|Playboy]]|pages= 115}}</ref>\n\nLynn and her brothers were placed with her father and his new family; in total there were eight boys and Lynn in the house. When Lynn was eleven, her father died of [[alcoholism]] and heart failure. As a teenager, Lynn self-described her change as going from \"pudgy kind of bucktoothed\" tomboy to a \"rocking little body\".<ref name=Playboy115/> She started doing fitness modeling, bikini modeling, and hot body contests. She relocated to Hollywood and became a regular at the clubs on [[Sunset Strip]].<ref name=Playboy115/>\n\n== Career ==\nLynn was a bikini and figure model in Los Angeles in the early 1980s; following this she was featured in nude magazine photo spreads for ''[[Penthouse (magazine)|Penthouse]]'', ''[[Hustler]]'', ''[[Chic (magazine)|Chic]]'', ''[[High Society (magazine)|High Society]]'' and ''[[Club (magazine)|Club]]'' magazines. Lynn made the transition from nude modeling to pornographic films with an appearance in [[Bobby Hollander]]'s 1983 feature ''Personal Touch 3'' in a scene with Craig Roberts.<ref name=Playboy115/><ref name=\"AVN83\">{{cite web | url= http://www.avn.com/porn-stars/Amber-Lynn-218515.html | title=Amber Lynn | accessdate=January 12, 2015 | date=January 12, 2015 | publisher=[[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]}}</ref> In 1983, shortly after her photo spread appeared in ''Penthouse'' magazine, she went to an audition for a movie where the director was a well-known porn veteran. There, in an effort to calm her nervousness, the director offered Lynn a pipe with some [[Crack cocaine|freebase cocaine]]. It was her first encounter with the drug; she later described the feeling of being as \"It's as if the birds are singing. The light is brighter. All of a sudden I'm no longer this gangly nervous teenager. I'm sitting there going 'Oh wow!{{'\"}}.<ref name=Playboy116>{{cite journal|author= Mike Sager|date=September 2011|title= The Porn Identity|journal= [[Playboy (magazine)|Playboy]]|pages= 116}}</ref>\n\nLynn was the first female performer to open the door for adult film stars to be featured in dance touring, being recognized for this accomplishment throughout the United States and Canada.  Lynn was the highest paid female performer on the [[strip club]] circuit, making $32,000 a week.<ref>Stripper Magazine Volume 10, Issue 1.  Jan/Feb 1998</ref>\n\nLynn has had roles in non-adult films such as ''[[Evils of the Night]]'' (1985) and ''[[52 Pick-Up]]'' (1986), and in the television program ''[[The Man Show]]'' and guest starred as herself in Lionsgate's ''[[Who's Jenna...?]]'' (2018).\n\nFor her 28th birthday in 1992, Lynn hosted a benefit birthday party at the Bel Age hotel in [[Beverly Hills]]. The benefit was in honor of The Youth AIDS Foundation of [[Los Angeles]], an organization providing housing and assistance for helping runaways get off the streets and for teenagers with [[HIV]], which was about to go under.<ref name='LAFR'>{{cite news | first=David | last=Fox | coauthors= | title=Adult-Film Star's Party to Benefit Youth AIDS Group Fund-raising: A birthday bash for Amber Lynn will raise money for a struggling organization. | date=August 28, 1992 | publisher= | url =https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/61619903.html?dids=61619903:61619903&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Aug+28%2C+1992&author=DAVID+J.+FOX&pub=Los+Angeles+Times+(pre-1997+Fulltext)&edition=&startpage=2&desc=Adult-Film+S | work =Los Angeles Times | pages = | accessdate = March 21, 2008 | language = }}</ref> An August 1992 issue of ''[[The Los Angeles Times]]'' quoted her statement on page two: \"Let's give them food, clothing and shelter and we'll worry about role models later\", alongside a shot of her dressed in a formal gown, holding an infant girl. This was a breakthrough moment for how the adult industry was viewed by the mainstream concerning its crossover involvement in children's organizations, as never before had a children's organization knowingly accepted support from the adult entertainment industry.<ref name='LATEHRMAN'>{{cite news | first=Mark | last=Ehrman | coauthors= | title=Exposing the Stars | date=September 4, 1992 | publisher= | url =https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/61637547.html?dids=61637547:61637547&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Sep+4%2C+1992&author=MARK+EHRMAN&pub=Los+Angeles+Times+(pre-1997+Fulltext)&edition=&startpage=5&desc=Exposing+the+S | work =The Los Angeles Times | pages = | accessdate = March 21, 2008 | language = }}</ref>\n\nLynn has opposed the Los Angeles \"Safer Sex in the Adult-Film Industry\" initiative, which mandates that actors in adult films shot in Los Angeles County use condoms. She has been involved in the first charity to accept contributions from the adult film industry, Youth AIDS Foundation of Los Angeles, since 1992.{{fact|date=June 2018}} She also helps other charities such as Childhood Cancer Awareness, The Southern California Toy Run and Janie\u2019s Fund, [[Steven Tyler]]'s new organization.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/amber-lynn-exposed-porn-star-best-work-article-1.2436546?cid=bitly#_gus&_gucid=article|title=Amber Lynn exposed: Porn star says best work yet to come|last=Parco|first=Nicolas|date=November 16, 2015|work=New York Daily News|accessdate=November 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\nLynn hosts a weekly [[talk show]] called ''Rock\u2019N'SeXXXy UnCensored'' on LATalkRadio.com and Stitcher.com.<ref name=2014AVNRadioshow>{{cite web|title=Wicked Girl Samantha Saint on Amber Lynn's Radio Show Tonight|url=http://business.avn.com/company-news/Wicked-Girl-Samantha-Saint-on-Amber-Lynn-s-Radio-Show-Tonight-554368.html|publisher=Adult Video News|accessdate=April 4, 2014}}</ref> She is a member of the [[Adult Video News]] (AVN) Hall of Fame and was awarded a Lifetime Achievement Award from the [[Free Speech Coalition]]. She continues to perform as an adult actress.\n\n== Personal life ==\nAmber Lynn is the sister of porn actor [[Buck Adams]]. <ref name=Sullivan> {{cite web|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/AVN-Hall-of-Famer-Buck-Adams-Dies-55560.html |title=AVN Hall of Famer Buck Adams Dies |last=Sullivan |first=David |date=October 28, 2008 |publisher=AVN.com |accessdate=June 19, 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100719223602/http://business.avn.com/articles/AVN-Hall-of-Famer-Buck-Adams-Dies-55560.html |archivedate=July 19, 2010 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> Lynn met porn actor [[Jamie Gillis]] on the set of her second-ever pornographic film, and the two began a long-time relationship.<ref name=Playboy116/>\n\nLynn had her first experience with cocaine on a porn set very early in her career.<ref name=Playboy116 /> She eventually became addicted to cocaine, a drug addiction that lasted for nearly two decades. She once said, \"I started out drinking [[Ketel One]] and slicing off crystals of Peruvian rock. I wound up broken down, drinking Kamchatka Vodka out of a half-pint stashed in the bottom of my purse, with my crack pipe stuffed in the lining of my jacket\".<ref name=Playboy116/> She has been clean and sober since 2000, and occasionally works as a personal recovery assistant, helping addicts to detox. She also works in mainstream acting roles, as a [[webcam model]] on one of the largest cam sites online, and as a real estate agent specializing in luxury homes.<ref name= Playboy116/>\n\n== Notable TV guest appearances ==\n* ''[[The Man Show]]'' \u2013 \"Hypnotist\" (episode 2.20) February 4, 2001\n* ''[[Frontline (PBS)|Frontline]]'' \u2013 \"Death of a Porn Queen\", June 1987\n\n== Awards ==\n* 1987 [[XRCO Award]] \u2013 Best Supporting Actress \u2013 ''Taboo 5'' <ref name='rame'>{{cite news | title=rame awards list | url =http://www.rame.net/library/lists/best.html | accessdate = December 16, 2007 | language = }}</ref>\n* 1993 [[Hot d'Or]] \u2013 Lifetime Achievement Award\n* 1996 [[XRCO Hall of Fame]] inductee<ref name='XRCO'>{{cite news|title=XRCO Hall of Fame |url=http://www.bwdl.net/XRCO-2/hall.htm |accessdate=December 16, 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720064742/http://www.bwdl.net/XRCO-2/hall.htm |archivedate=July 20, 2011 |df=mdy }}</ref>\n* 2001 [[AVN Hall of Fame]] inductee<ref name='AVN HOF'>{{cite news | first= | last= | coauthors= | title=AVN Hall of Fame | date= | publisher= | url =http://www.avnawards.com/index.php?center=hall-of-fame | work = | pages = | accessdate = December 16, 2007 | language = }}</ref>\n* 2003 [[Free Speech Coalition]] \u2013 Lifetime Achievement Award<ref>{{cite news |url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/Free-Speech-Coalition-Celebrates-16th-Night-Of-The-Stars-31469.html |title=Free Speech Coalition Celebrates 16th Night Of The Stars |date=July 14, 2003 |accessdate= September 26, 2014}}</ref>\n* 2007 [[Adam Film World]] Guide \u2013 Lifetime Achievement Award<ref name='AFWG'>{{cite news | first= | last= | coauthors= | title=Adam Film World Guild | date= | publisher= | url =http://www.cavr.com/adam2007.htm | work = | pages = | accessdate = July 29, 2008 | language = }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Amber Lynn}}\n* {{official}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* {{iafd name}}\n* {{afdb name}}\n* {{Twitter}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lynn, Amber}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:American female erotic dancers]]\n[[Category:American erotic dancers]]\n[[Category:American female adult models]]\n[[Category:American pornographic film actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Newport Beach, California]]\n[[Category:Pornographic film actors from California]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Webcam models]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "s