ame=twins/>\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Brooklyn Center, Minnesota|Brooklyn Center]], [[United States]] since 5 July 1993<ref name=twins/>\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Boston]], [[United States]] since 21 May 1996<ref name=twins/>\n*{{flagicon|PRC}} [[Shenyang]], [[China]] since 22 May 2000<ref name=twins/>\n*{{flagicon|ARM}} [[Gyumri]], [[Armenia]] since 23 November 2000<ref name=twins/>\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Philadelphia]], [[United States]] since 6 April 2002<ref name=twins/>\n*{{flagicon|RUS}} [[Saint Petersburg]], [[Russia]], since 30 October 2002<ref name=twins/>\n*{{flagicon|UKR}} [[Dnipro]], [[Ukraine]] since 18 April 2003<ref name=twins/>\n*{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Venice]], [[Italy]] since 17 July 2003<ref name=twins/>\n*{{flagicon|PRC}} [[Dongguan]], [[China]] since 24 October 2008<ref name=twins/>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Battle of Thessalonica (disambiguation)|Battle of Thessalonica]] (fourteen events at various times)\n* [[Macedonians (Greeks)]]\n* [[Mount Chortiatis]], above the city\n* [[Lake Koroneia]], 14&nbsp;km from the city\n* [[Delta, Thessaloniki|Delta]] of [[Vardar|Axios]] National Park, west of the city\n\n==References==\n\n===Notes===\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* Apostolos Papagiannopoulos,''Monuments of Thessaloniki'', Rekos Ltd, date unknown.\n* Apostolos P. Vacalopoulos, ''A History of Thessaloniki'', Institute for Balkan Studies,1972.\n* John R. Melville-Jones, 'Venice and Thessalonica 1423\u20131430 Vol I, The Venetian Accounts, Vol. II, the Greek Accounts, Unipress, Padova, 2002 and 2006 (the latter work contains English translations of accounts of the events of this period by St [[Symeon of Thessaloniki]] and [[John Anagnostes]]).\n* ''Thessaloniki: Tourist guide and street map'', A. Kessopoulos, Malliare\u00cc\"s-Paideia, 1988.\n* [[Mark Mazower]], ''Salonica, City of Ghosts: Christians, Muslims and Jews, 1430\u20131950'', 2004, {{ISBN|0-375-41298-0}}.\n* Naar, Devin E. ''Jewish Salonica: Between the Ottoman Empire and\nModern Greece.'' Stanford Studies in Jewish History and Culture\nSeries. Stanford Stanford University Press, 2016. 400 pp. {{ISBN|978-1-5036-0008-9}}.\n* Eugenia Russell, ''St Demetrius of Thessalonica; Cult and Devotion in the Middle Ages'', Peter Lang, Oxford, 2010. {{ISBN|978-3-0343-0181-7}}\n* James C. Skedros, ''Saint Demetrios of Thessaloniki: Civic Patron and Divine Protector, 4th-7Th Centuries'' (Harvard Theological Studies), Trinity Press International (1999).\n* Vilma Hastaoglou-Martinidis (ed.), ''Restructuring the City: International Urban Design Competitions for Thessaloniki'', Andreas Papadakis, 1999.\n* Matthieu Ghilardi, Dynamiques spatiales et reconstitutions pal\u00e9og\u00e9ographiques de la plaine de Thessalonique (Gr\u00e8ce) \u00e0 l'Holoc\u00e8ne r\u00e9cent, 2007. Th\u00e8se de Doctorat de l'Universit\u00e9 de Paris 12 Val-de-Marne, 475 p.\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons}}\n{{wikivoyage|Thessaloniki}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n\n===Government===\n* [https://thessaloniki.gr/?lang=en Municipality of Thessaloniki]\n* [http://www.thpa.gr/ Thessaloniki Port Authority]\n* [http://www.oasth.gr/ \u039f\u0391\u03a3\u0398 \u2013 Organisation of Urban Transport of Thessaloniki] (Greek & English)\n\n===Tourism===\n* {{YouTube|tALS0WZqi_Y|You in Thessaloniki}}: Official promotional video for Thessaloniki by the [[Greek National Tourism Organization]]\n* [http://www.visitgreece.gr/en/main_cities/thessaloniki Thessaloniki] The Official website of the Greek National Tourism Organisation\n\n===Cultural===\n* [http://www.tch.gr/ Thessaloniki Concert Hall Organisation]\n* [http://www.filmfestival.gr/ Thessaloniki Film Festival]\n* [http://www.saloniki.org/ Thessaloniki Info & Links]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080402233222/http://www.thessaloniki360.com/ Thessaloniki360 Virtual City Guide]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100910051528/http://tsimiski.gr/ Thessaloniki Tsimiski.gr street]\n\n===Events===\n* [http://www.thessaloniki2012.gr/ Thessaloniki 2012] (celebrations for the 100 years of the incorporation of the city to Greece)\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120611080819/http://www.thessaloniki2014.eu/ Thessaloniki 2014] (official website of Thessaloniki European Youth Capital 2014)\n\n===Local guides===\n* [https://www.xo.gr/dir-loc-geo/Prefecture%20of%20Thessaloniki/Thessaloniki/?lang=en Greek Local Yellow Pages of Thessaloniki]\n\n{{Greek Macedonia}}\n{{Kallikratis-Central Macedonia}}\n{{Thessaloniki div}}\n{{European Capital of Culture}}\n{{European Youth Capital}}\n{{World Heritage Sites in Greece}}\n{{Landmarks of Thessaloniki}}\n{{Neighbourhoods in Thessaloniki}}\n{{Museums in Thessaloniki}}\n{{Capitals of Peripheries of Greece}}\n{{Second Journey of Paul of Tarsus}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n<!--[[Category:Mediterranean]] covered via Category:Port cities in Greece-->\n[[Category:Thessaloniki| ]]\n[[Category:Geography of ancient Mygdonia]]\n[[Category:Greek regional capitals]]\n[[Category:Historic Jewish communities]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean port cities and towns in Greece]]\n[[Category:Municipalities of Central Macedonia]]\n[[Category:New Testament cities]]\n[[Category:Pauline churches]]\n[[Category:Populated coastal places in Greece]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in the 4th century BC]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Thessaloniki (regional unit)]]\n[[Category:Port cities of the Aegean Sea]]\n[[Category:Capitals of Greek states]]\n[[Category:Fortified settlements]]\n[[Category:World Heritage Sites in Greece|Thessaloniki, Paleochristian and Byzantine Monuments]]\n[[Category:310s BC establishments]]\n[[Category:Ancient Greek archaeological sites in Greece]]\n[[Category:Archaeological sites in Macedonia (Greece)]]\n[[Category:4th-century BC establishments in Greece]]\n", "name_user": "Skoulikomirmigotripa", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thessaloniki"}
