rtive after Batts' death in 2013.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== Activism ==\nFlores is supportive of her description as a [[Big Beautiful Woman|BBW]] performer but chooses not to perform in traditional BBW porn, as she believes that it is derogatory towards its BBW performers.<ref name=\":1\" /> She instead chooses directors and performers that she feels will represent larger women in a desirable and positive light.\n\nIn a 2015 article with ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'' Flores stated that she wants her work to show plus size women \"that we are worthy of pleasure and desirability\" and that she wants to reclaim the term \"fat\" to have a positive connotation instead of a negative one.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== Writing ==\nIn 2013 Flores co-authored and published a fine art book called ''Fat Girl'' with her husband just prior to his death. Published by Rare Bird Books, it represents a twelve-year collaboration the two as model and photographer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://therumpus.net/2013/08/the-rumpus-interview-with-april-flores-and-carlos-batts/|title=The Rumpus Interview with April Flores and Carlos Batts|date=2013-08-30|work=The Rumpus.net|access-date=2017-04-28|language=en-US}}</ref> The book was Batts' fourth publication.<ref name=\"Staff 2013 22\"/>\n\nApril Flores also contributed a chapter to ''The Feminist Porn Book: The Politics of Producing Pleasure''. In her chapter, \"Being Fatty D: Size, Beauty, and Embodiment in the Adult Industry,\" Flores talks about how she came into the porn industry and her work to portray big women as sexual and desirable.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nFlores was married to Carlos Batts for 10 years until his death on October 22, 2013.<ref name=BattsDeath>{{cite web|url= http://www.xbiz.com/news/170418|title= Carlos Batts Passes Away|accessdate= 2013-10-27|author= Dan Miller|date= 2013-10-23|publisher= [[XBIZ]]}}</ref> After his death a fundraiser called \"Remembering Carlos\" was hosted for April on November 13, 2013.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.fattyd.com/remembering-carlos-a-fundraiser-for-april-flores/|title=Remembering Carlos: A Fundraiser for April Flores|website=April Flores Fatty D|access-date=December 7, 2017}}</ref> A silent art auction and PayPal account were set up to aid April in costly medical bills.<ref name=\":4\" />\n\n==Significance and Other Ventures==\nIn 2009, [[sex toy]] company Topco released Voluptuous Pussy, a life-size inflatable doll named after Flores's [[vagina]] but modeled as an exact replica of her entire body.<ref name=\"bizarretoy\"/><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sfgate.com/living/article/Her-Plastic-Vagina-Violet-Blue-Porn-star-April-2476173.php|title=Her Plastic Vagina / Violet Blue: Porn star April Flores tells all about her body part sex toy|last=Blue|first=Violet|date=September 24, 2009|website=SF Gate|access-date=March 2, 2017}}</ref>  It is touted as \u201cthe first realistic plus-size sex toy\u201d, and it is made out of Cyberskin material.<ref name=\"bizarretoy\"/><ref name=\":0\" />\n\nFlores was the first plus-sized porn star to be on the cover of [[AVN (magazine)|AVN]] magazine <ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.laweekly.com/arts/april-flores-the-plus-size-porn-star-4183760|title=April Flores, the Plus-Size Porn Star|last=Seidman|first=Lila|date=2013-08-06|work=L.A. Weekly|access-date=2017-04-27}}</ref> and the first BBW to win an [[AVN Award|AVN award]].<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nFlores has her own show on [[Sirius XM Holdings|SiriusXM]]'s [[Vivid Entertainment|Vivid]] Radio called \"Voluptuous Life\" where she and her listeners talk about sex and educate each other.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=https://aipdaily.com/interview-with-april-flores-part-1/|title=Interview with April Flores Part 1 {{!}} AIPdaily.com|date=2014-10-29|work=AIPdaily.com|access-date=2017-04-28|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nApril's website, ''Fat Girl Fantasies'', launched in Spring of 2015. Her website honors her relationship with her late husband, but also depicts \"fat women as sexual beings\" and reveals their sexual fantasies.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:55%;\"\n|-\n!width=\"7%\"|Year\n!width=\"7%\"|Ceremony\n!width=\"42%\"|Category\n!width=\"36%\"|Work\n!width=\"8%\"|Result\n|-\n|align=center|2010\n|align=center|[[Feminist Porn Award|FPA]]\n|Heartthrob of the Year<ref>{{cite magazine|url= http://business.avn.com/articles/video/Feminist-Porn-Awards-Winners-Announced-394741.html|title= Feminist Porn Awards Winners Announced|accessdate= 2013-10-27|date= 2010-04-10|magazine= [[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]}}</ref>\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|align=center|2011\n|align=center|[[AVN Award|AVN]]\n|Crossover Star of the Year<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707194245/http://avnawards.avn.com/2011_nominations2.pdf|title=Nominations for the 2011 AVN Awards|work=[[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]|archivedate=July 7, 2011|url=http://avnawards.avn.com/2011_nominations2.pdf|accessdate=December 3, 2013}}</ref>\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|align=center|2012\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|BBW FanFest\n|Creative BBW of the Year<ref>{{cite magazine|url= http://business.avn.com/company-news/2012-BBWFanFest-Awards-Winners-Announced-482475.html|title= 2012 BBWFanFest Awards Winners Announced|accessdate= 2013-10-27|date= 2012-07-25|magazine=AVN}}</ref>\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|align=center|2013\n|Hall of Fame<ref>{{cite magazine|url= http://business.avn.com/company-news/BBW-FanFest-Announces-2013-Award-Nominations-511689.html|title= BBW FanFest Announces 2013 Award Nominations|accessdate= 2013-10-27|date= 2013-04-02|magazine=AVN}}</ref>\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|align=center|2014\n|align=center rowspan=2|AVN\n|rowspan=2|[[AVN Award for BBW Performer of the Year|BBW Performer of the Year]]<ref name=\"avnwin2014\">{{cite magazine|url= http://business.avn.com/articles/video/AVN-Announces-the-Winners-of-the-2014-AVN-Award