women]]\u2019s magazines like ''[[Bizarre (magazine)|Bizarre]]'',<ref name=\"bizarrecover\"/> ''[[Juggs]]''<ref name=\"officialabout\"/> and ''Big Butt Magazine'' (the latter of which she appeared on the cover on two separate occasions). In 2000, she began doing photo shoots for photographer Carlos Batts.<ref name=\"20Q\">[http://www.hotmoviesforher.com/interviews/20-questions-with-april-flores.html 20 Questions With April Flores | HotmoviesforHer.com] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120608100029/http://www.hotmoviesforher.com/interviews/20-questions-with-april-flores.html |date=2012-06-08 }}. Retrieved December 7, 2011.</ref> They eventually moved from photos to [[amateur film]]; at one point Batts also had fellow [[pornographic film actor|porn actress]] [[Belladonna (actress)|Belladonna]] as one of his clients. Belladonna and Flores began doing photo shoots together; this led to the two appearing in the film ''Evil Pink 2''. This movie was Flores\u2019s first filmed sex scene<ref name=\"20Q\"/> as well as her first actual sexual experience; she lost her on-screen [[virginity]] to Belladonna on film.<ref name=\"bizarrecover\"/> Despite this, Flores considers ''Alter Ego'' to be her first official film.<ref name=\"20Q\"/> She also considers herself an \u201cerotic entertainer\u201d rather than a porn star.\n\n== Coming Out as a Porn Star ==\nIn 2005, Flores was invited to perform with Belladonna.<ref name=\":1\" /> The film was April's first porn scene with a woman.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/sex-love/news/a37554/april-flores-bbw-porn-performer-fat-acceptance/|title=I Want People to See Fat Women as Sexual Beings. Because We Are.|last=Wischhover|first=Cheryl|date=March 10, 2015|website=Cosmopolitan|access-date=March 2, 2017}}</ref> Flores confessed that she wore a wig during the performance so that if anyone brought it up she could deny that \"that was not [her]!\"<ref name=\":2\" /> However, Flores enjoyed performing and was later invited to do more scenes.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nApril's father passed away in 2001, so she never came out to him.<ref name=\":2\" /> Flores admitted that she was scared to come out as a porn star to her mother. However, her mother was supportive of her career and became more supportive after Batts' death in 2013.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== Activism ==\nFlores is supportive of her description as a [[Big Beautiful Woman|BBW]] performer but chooses not to perform in traditional BBW porn, as she believes that it is derogatory towards its BBW performers.<ref name=\":1\" /> She instead chooses directors and performers that she feels will represent larger women in a desirable and positive light.\n\nIn a 2015 article with ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'' Flores stated that she wants her work to show plus size women \"that we are worthy of pleasure and desirability\" and that she wants to reclaim the term \"fat\" to have a positive connotation instead of a negative one.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== Writing ==\nIn 2013 Flores co-authored and published a fine art book called ''Fat Girl'' with her husband just prior to his death. Published by Rare Bird Books, it represents a twelve-year collaboration the two as model and photographer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://therumpus.net/2013/08/the-rumpus-interview-with-april-flores-and-carlos-batts/|title=The Rumpus Interview with April Flores and Carlos Batts|date=2013-08-30|work=The Rumpus.net|access-date=2017-04-28|language=en-US}}</ref> The book was Batts' fourth publication.<ref name=\"Staff 2013 22\"/>\n\nApril Flores also contributed a chapter to ''The Feminist Porn Book: The Politics of Producing Pleasure''. In her chapter, \"Being Fatty D: Size, Beauty, and Embodiment in the Adult Industry,\" Flores talks about how she came into the porn industry and her work to portray big women as sexual and desirable.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nFlores was married to Carlos Batts for 10 years until his death on